The paper deals with the design of quasi-complementary sequence sets (QCSS) for multicarrier code-division multiple-access applications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves optimization techniques to derive a new weight vector, which falls under the category of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of circulant matrices, which is a common tool in multimedia processing (cs.MM).
